        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1968-06-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1968-06-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="249"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d249">
                <head>249. Letter From Chairman <persName corresp="#p_KAN1" type="from"
                        >Kosygin</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_JLB1" type="to"
                        >Johnson</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d249fn1">Source: Johnson Library, National
                        Security File, Intelligence File, Arms Control Messages Exchanged Between
                        President <persName corresp="#p_JLB1">Johnson</persName> and Chairman,
                            <gloss target="#t_USSR1">USSR</gloss>, Vol. I, Box 11.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Moscow</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1968-06-27"
                            >June 27, 1968</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">Dear Mr. President:</p>
                <p>My colleagues and I have carefully considered your letter of June 22, 1968,<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d249fn2">
                        <ref target="#d248">Document 248</ref>.</note> concerning talks on strategic
                    offensive and defensive nuclear weapons delivery systems. We are prepared to
                    publish in the Soviet press and over the radio on July 1 the following statement
                    of the Soviet Government: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“On the forthcoming talks on questions of curbing the strategic arms
                            race.</p>
                        <p>“An agreement has been reached between the Government of the <gloss
                                target="#t_USSR1">USSR</gloss> and the <gloss target="#t_USA1"
                                >USA</gloss> to enter in the nearest future into talks on limitation
                            and reduction of offensive strategic nuclear weapons delivery systems as
                            well as systems of defense against ballistic missiles.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>We have no doubt that a statement in such a spirit made by our Governments
                    should, undoubtedly, also further the task of inducing the adherence of the
                    greatest number of states to the non-proliferation treaty.</p>
                <p>Sincerely,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KAN1">
                            <hi rend="strong">A. Kosygin</hi>
                        </persName>
                        <note n="3" xml:id="d249fn3">Printed from a copy that bears this typed
                            signature.</note>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
